<section class="philosophy" id="about">
  <div class="philo-deco philo-deco-1">
    <svg width="220" height="220" viewBox="0 0 220 220" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <circle cx="110" cy="110" r="100" fill="none" stroke="#FAF3E3" stroke-width="3" stroke-dasharray="4 8"/>
      <circle cx="110" cy="110" r="60" fill="#F5C13D"/>
      <path d="M85 95 Q110 75 135 95" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round"/>
      <circle cx="95" cy="115" r="4" fill="#1A1A1A"/>
      <circle cx="125" cy="115" r="4" fill="#1A1A1A"/>
      <path d="M95 130 Q110 145 125 130" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round"/>
    </svg>
  </div>
  <div class="philo-deco philo-deco-2">
    <svg width="180" height="180" viewBox="0 0 180 180" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <path d="M90 10 L100 70 L160 80 L110 110 L130 170 L90 140 L50 170 L70 110 L20 80 L80 70 Z"
            fill="#FF6B47" stroke="#FAF3E3" stroke-width="3"/>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <div class="section-head reveal">
    <div>
      <p class="section-label">The philosophy</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Why simple<br><em>always wins.</em></h2>
    </div>
    <p class="section-aside">Ancient scribes, wandering poets, and field scientists kept pocket notebooks. Not because it was fashionable. Because it worked.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="philo-grid">
    <div class="philo-item reveal">
      <div class="philo-num">01</div>
      <div class="philo-content">
        <h3>The pocket constraint is a gift</h3>
        <p>A small page forces you to choose. Every word earns its space. Brevity becomes a writing practice in itself.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="philo-item reveal">
      <div class="philo-num">02</div>
      <div class="philo-content">
        <h3>Grid pages free the mind</h3>
        <p>Not lined. Not blank. Grid. It holds structure loosely — for words, sketches, maps, lists that turn into poems.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="philo-item reveal">
      <div class="philo-num">03</div>
      <div class="philo-content">
        <h3>Ancient notebooks were the internet</h3>
        <p>Roman wax tablets. Persian poetry diaries. Indian kavyagrantha. Knowledge lived in physical books carried on the body.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="philo-item reveal">
      <div class="philo-num">04</div>
      <div class="philo-content">
        <h3>Complexity is the enemy of writing</h3>
        <p>The best system is the one you actually use. A notebook costs no subscription. It needs no battery. It never syncs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

